ethodologically discussed and empirically demonstrated: with respect to ergativity, the ergative-absolutive cross-referencing pattern on the morphological level, noun-verb distinction and the acquisition of body-part locatives in the early lexicon, and the role of semantic properties and cultural context in language acquisition and socialization. This book makes important claims regarding the methodology of cross-linguistic studies as well as the results of these studies and the comparative method used in the book (structural and discursive factors in language acquisition, cross-linguistic relationships and variation).  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aIndians of Central AmericaxLanguages. 0aLanguage acquisition. 4aMesoamerika. 4aSpracherwerb. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh  aIndigenous languages, Mesoamerica, Language Acquisition.1 aBrown, Penelope, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCarreón, Carlos Carrillo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLópez, Paula Gómez, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMateo, Pedro, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPfeiler, Barbara, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPfeiler, Barbara, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aPye, Clifton, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 ade León, Lourdes, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 ade López, Kristine Jensen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1z978311023857008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe G